text:
Hi, if I have a custom theme (and associated published webpages) currently on a Developer sandbox account, is there a proper way to migrate everything over to our main HubSpot account? Was trying to find an official procedure for migration between accounts, but wasn't sure where to look.

(Ideally, step one would be to have everything migrated over to a subdomain first, like <http://alpha.company.com|alpha.company.com>, and once it all checks out to be working properly there, then move it over to production at <http://www.company.com|www.company.com>)

I had the same problem - solved by removing the "Pretty Diff" beautifier included in the autogenerated config from Unibeautifier's <https://assistant.unibeautify.com/#/setup|setup wizard > :slightly_smiling_face:
